{
  "title": "ColorGradient",
  "description": "Piecewise-linear color gradient sampled by lifetime ratio `t` in `[0, 1]`. Keyframes are stored sorted by `t`; sampling outside the range returns the nearest endpoint color. Like Curve, the last accessed segment is cached so monotonically advancing `t` is O(1) amortised. Two output paths: - evaluate — writes into a `Color` instance (own scratch by default). - evaluateRgba — returns the packed `0xAABBGGRR` u32 directly, skipping the Color object. Use this in tight per-particle inner loops that write into a `Uint32Array` instance buffer.",
